[
    {
        "content": "<p>Why do we not have Ordinal.succ defeq to Order.succ (currently Ordinal.succ does not exist)?</p>",
        "id": 526292209,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751227918
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are you proposing to add</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ordinal</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ordinal</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ordinal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Order</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>for the dot notation?</p>",
        "id": 526292309,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751228034
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>note that Ordinal.succ used to exist, it was removed with the order refactor</p>",
        "id": 526292342,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751228064
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hmm probably the same reason why we don't want A+B as ideal then</p>",
        "id": 526292370,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1751228078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why can't you just add one?</p>",
        "id": 526292377,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751228081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Addition is not commutative, so you have to be a bit careful there.</p>",
        "id": 526292444,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751228131
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I think <code>o + 1</code> is equal to <code>o.succ</code></p>",
        "id": 526292468,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751228149
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, do <code>o + 1</code> I mean</p>",
        "id": 526292469,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751228149
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>1 + o = o</code> for <code>o</code> infinite</p>",
        "id": 526292501,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1751228170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I think it's the same as for <code>Nat</code>, <code>succ</code> is in some ways more basic</p>",
        "id": 526292507,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751228175
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and they aren't defeq</p>",
        "id": 526292516,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1751228183
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>wait how can o+1 not be defeq to succ o</p>",
